  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations for NAICS 541511: Custom Computer Programming Services totaled $7.1B in FY2026 to date, with 4,110 awards and an average award size of $1.7M. Obligations fell 31.0% year over year. From FY21 through FY25, annual obligations ranged from $8.6B to $10.8B, with FY24 at $10.8B and FY25 at $10.3B before the FY2026 to date total of $7.1B. The Department of Defense accounted for the largest share of FY2026 to date obligations at $3B, followed by the Department of Health and Human Services at $956M and the Department of Veterans Affairs at $750M. Vendor receipts in FY2026 to date were led by PALANTIR USG INC at $867M and GENERAL DYNAMICS INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY, INC. at $564M, with BOOZ ALLEN HAMILTON INC at $310M and other firms rounding out the top ten. These figures are contract obligations and represent fiscal year to date totals for FY2026.",
