        "body": "FY2026 to date obligations are $7.1B, which is lower than each of FY21 through FY25. FY25 obligations were $10.3B and FY24 obligations were $10.8B. Obligations fell 31.0% year over year."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and vendors dominate FY2026 to date obligations?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense is the largest buyer with $3B in obligations, followed by the Department of Health and Human Services at $956M and the Department of Veterans Affairs at $750M. The top vendor is PALANTIR USG INC at $867M, followed by GENERAL DYNAMICS INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY, INC. at $564M and BOOZ ALLEN HAMILTON INC at $310M."
      }
